                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 814.51/240.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-05-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 1, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The President says that the British Government flatly refused the request of the
                    Guatemalan Chargé d’Affaires at London for time and stated that they would
                    insist upon the restoration of the coffee tax regardless of any arrangement
                    between the Guatemalan Government and the bankers.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
